---
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Install MCP — @melis-ai/x402-tools-mcp"
  description="How to install @melis-ai/x402-tools-mcp in Claude Desktop, Cursor, Claude Code, and Continue. One command gives your agent access to 16 x402 utility tools."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Docs', url: 'https://agents.melis.ai/docs/install-mcp' }, { name: 'Install MCP', url: 'https://agents.melis.ai/docs/install-mcp' }]}
>
  <div class="container doc-page">
    <div class="doc-header">
      <a href="/docs/x402-payment" class="doc-nav-link">Docs</a>
      <h1>Install MCP</h1>
      <p class="doc-sub">
        One command. All 18 services as MCP tools. Works in any MCP-aware agent environment.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Quick start</h2>
      <pre><code>npx @melis-ai/x402-tools-mcp</code></pre>
      <p>Run this once to verify the server starts. Then configure your agent tool to use it.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Claude Desktop</h2>
      <p>Add to your <code>claude_desktop_config.json</code>:</p>
      <p class="path-note">
        macOS: <code>~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code><br />
        Windows: <code>%APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json</code>
      </p>
      <pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "x402-tools": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@melis-ai/x402-tools-mcp"],
      "env": {
        "X402_INTERNAL_KEY": "your-issued-key-if-applicable"
      }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>
      <p>Restart Claude Desktop. The 16 tools will appear in the tool list.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Cursor</h2>
      <p>Open Cursor Settings → MCP → Add server:</p>
      <pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "x402-tools": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@melis-ai/x402-tools-mcp"]
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>
      <p>Save and reload Cursor. Tools will appear in the Cursor agent tool list.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Claude Code (CLI)</h2>
      <pre><code>claude mcp add x402-tools -- npx @melis-ai/x402-tools-mcp</code></pre>
      <p>
        Or add the JSON above to <code>~/.claude/mcp.json</code> (global) or
        <code>.claude/mcp.json</code> in your project root.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Continue (VS Code / JetBrains)</h2>
      <p>Add to your <code>~/.continue/config.json</code>:</p>
      <pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": [
    {
      "name": "x402-tools",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@melis-ai/x402-tools-mcp"]
    }
  ]
}`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Available tools</h2>
      <p>After install, these tool names are callable in your agent:</p>
      <pre><code>{`list_services         — free, returns the full catalogue
cacheserve            — $0.001
docconvert_text       — $0.001
schemagate            — $0.001
notifyrelay_webhook   — $0.001
promptguard           — $0.002
notifyrelay_telegram  — $0.002
structextract         — $0.002
docconvert_pdf        — $0.005
linkrisk              — $0.005
markdownopt           — $0.005
notifyrelay_email     — $0.005
linksafe              — $0.010
scrapepay             — $0.010
pdf_render            — $0.490`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Environment variables</h2>
      <table class="env-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Variable</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>X402_PAYMENT_HEADER</code></td>
            <td>Pre-signed x402 payment token. Set this if your wallet handles payment externally.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>X402_INTERNAL_KEY</code></td>
            <td>Bypass key for trusted internal callers. Skips the 402 flow entirely. Contact sean@melis.ai.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <div class="doc-nav-bottom">
      <a href="/docs/x402-payment">Next: x402 payment flow →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
.doc-page { padding-top: 4rem; padding-bottom: 4rem; max-width: 720px; }
.doc-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.doc-nav-link { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-3); margin-bottom: 1rem; display: block; }
h1 { font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
.doc-sub { color: var(--text-2); font-size: 15px; }
section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
section h2 { font-size: 1.125rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
section p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
.path-note { font-size: 13px !important; color: var(--text-3) !important; }
.env-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; }
.env-table th { text-align: left; padding: 8px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text-3); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
.env-table td { padding: 8px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light); color: var(--text-2); }
.doc-nav-bottom { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
.doc-nav-bottom a { font-size: 14px; color: var(--accent); }
</style>
